{
  "text": "Adaptiveopticsscanninglaserophthalmoscopy(AOSLO) uses adaptive optics to compensate for optical aberrations in living eyes, improving resolution of retinal images to a lateral resolution of approximately 2 m. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] Direct visualization of the cone mosaic in patients with retinal degenerations, combined with other imaging and diagnostic techniques, allows comparison of cone spacing with healthy individuals and can provide insight into the effects of different retinal degenerations on macular cones.",
  "correct_citation": {
